            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Did you try the `SourcePre` event?\r\n\r\nVim plugins are a collection of files which may be cross-referenced by other plugins. They are not isolated, so it might be difficult to meaningfully say \"this plugin was loaded\". And the namespaces are not \"owned\" by one plugin: any other plugin can modify another plugin's namespace.\r\n\r\nBram is flirting with the idea of  [half-baked dependency management](https://vimconf.org/2018/slides/Vim_From-hjkl-to-a-platform-for-plugins.pdf) (`PluginDepend()`, `PluginLoad()`).\r\n\r\nIf Vim decides to add more semantics around its \"packages\", we will merge that. Otherwise it's not worth our time to fork the behavior there.",
